    <h2 class="mb-20 mb-mob-34 term-tags fnt-24">Term Insurance Fundamentals </h2>
	<p>Term insurance is a type of life insurance in which the policyholder is covered for a specific period of
time, also known as the term of the policy. If the policyholder dies during the term, a death benefit
is paid to the designated beneficiaries. Term insurance is typically useful for providing for the
financial needs of the dependents in the event of the policyholders death. Premiums for term
insurance are generally lower than those for whole life insurance, as the coverage is for a limited
time period. In India, term insurance policies can have a term of 10, 20, or more years depending on
your requirements or insurance providers terms.
 </p>
 
